<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,769,2042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="338">
Remarks. This new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Rajmohana &amp; Narendran, 2006" authorityName="Rajmohana &amp; Narendran" authorityYear="2006" box="[593,1088,1913,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Basalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicus">
<emphasis box="[593,752,1913,1937]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="338">Basalys unicus</emphasis>
Rajmohana &amp; Narendran, 2006
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1151,1209,1913,1937]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="338">India</collectingCountry>
, but it can be separated from the latter by: antenna 12-segmented (11-segmented in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rajmohana &amp; Narendran" authorityYear="2006" box="[770,869,1949,1972]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Basalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicus">
<emphasis box="[770,869,1949,1972]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="338">B. unicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); head distinctly long than high in lateral view (almost quadrate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rajmohana &amp; Narendran" authorityYear="2006" box="[262,362,1983,2006]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Basalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicus">
<emphasis box="[262,362,1983,2006]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="338">B. unicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); notauli absent (present but faint in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rajmohana &amp; Narendran" authorityYear="2006" box="[756,856,1983,2006]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Basalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicus">
<emphasis box="[756,856,1983,2006]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="338">B. unicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
